An overview of the use of computers in learning and teaching school mathematics. The interest is concentrated on the dynamic geometry, computer algebra system programs used in Estonian schools, composing, searching and adapting study material.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the subject is to give an overview of  use of computers in learning and teaching school mathematics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Is able to find, differentiate and evaluate various computer programs and software for teaching mathematics.
Is able to use various computer programs and software for teaching mathematics, which are available at the Estonian schools.
Is able to compose and evaluate lesson plans.
Is able to find, adapt and create learning materials for studying mathematics using ICT tools.
